<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="387" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.61/29b</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-25T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>562. Please deliver following message to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">Francis</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>To-day’s press reports you have left Petrograd. Confirming
                                        previous instructions Department relies on your judgment as
                                        to leaving your post and taking measures requisite to
                                        safeguard staff and archives from falling into enemy hands.
                                        Seals, codes, cipher messages or translations should be
                                        taken with you or if this impossible should be burned and
                                        seals destroyed. Please repeat to Consuls Petrograd and
                                        Archangel.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <p>Consuls Moscow and Helsingfors have been sent like instructions
                                direct.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>